  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">K&apos;inal Antsetik A.C. (K&apos;inal), $290,442 over three years. K&apos;inal will offer training, assistance with productive projects, and programs in health, education and communication to indigenous women in Chiapas through improving Jolom Mayaetik, a textile cooperative, and founding the Women&apos;s Leadership Center. Some 350 members of approximately 14 community groups will participate in the project.</narrative>
